# S09: Landscape Fit & Final Polish

## Objective
Make every screen fit the smallest landscape phone **667×375** without scroll or clipping,
then a final quality pass + README update covering modes, the living character, and melodies.
Runs after S08 (needs both game screens to exist).

## Tasks
- [ ] S09-T01-LandscapeAudit.pd
- [ ] S09-T02-LandscapeGameLayout.pd
- [ ] S09-T03-LandscapeStartGameOver.pd
- [ ] S09-T04-LandscapePianoCompact.pd
- [ ] S09-T05-CrossDeviceQA.pd
- [ ] S09-T06-ReadmeUpdate.pd

## Landscape contract (667×375)

| Element | Rule |
|---|---|
| Score panel | One compact row, `py-0.5`, small badge |
| Mascot | `≤64px` height in landscape, or beside content (flex-row) |
| Note/ring (Find) | ring `≤80px`, compact VexFlow |
| Runner staff | reduced height; hit-line + ground still visible |
| Piano | compact / narrowed octave (C4–B4) if needed |
| Start / GameOver | `clamp()` fonts, no `text-5xl`, CTAs always visible |
| Safe area | respect `env(safe-area-inset-*)` |

## Definition of Done
- All screens (Start, Find, Runner, GameOver) pass 667×375 landscape: zero vertical scroll, no clipped CTAs.
- Touch targets ≥ 44px in landscape.
- README documents modes, character, melodies, landscape strategy, LLM usage.
- Zero console errors; `git commit` after each task.
